### Step 1 — Create order (copy order_id from response)
# @name checkout
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/checkout
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
    "buyer_id": "{{buyerId}}",
    "menu_store_id": "{{menuStoreId}}",
    "items": [
        {"menu_item_id": "c3d4e5f6-a7b8-9012-cdef-123456789012", "name": "Ban Mian", "quantity": 1, "unit_price": 500}
    ],
    "food_cost": 500,
    "delivery_fee": 350,
    "platform_fee": 10,
    "drop_off": {
        "latitude": 1.3521,
        "longitude": 103.8198,
        "address": "123 Orchard Road, Singapore 238867"
    }
}

###

# After Step 1: paste the order_id from the response below
@orderId = b7cccbe4-8c41-445a-ac22-30c80dbdf3c3

### Step 1b — Check order status (should be PENDING before accepting)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/{{orderId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 2 — Runner accepts the order (status: PENDING → ACCEPTED)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/orders/{{orderId}}/accept
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
    "runner_id": "{{runnerId}}"
}

###

### Step 3 — Buyer reports runner as MIA (status: ACCEPTED → MIA)
### Expected: 200 {"order_id": "...", "status": "MIA"}
### Side effects (via Kafka):
###   - Payment Management: full refund issued to buyer
###   - Delivery Management: location session closed
PUT {{baseUrl}}/orders/{{orderId}}/mia
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Verify — Check order status is MIA
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/{{orderId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
